data.name: Atalya
data.description: Must book in advance! Atalya Ein Mor was born and raised in the picturesque village of Ein Kerem. Following her work in renowned restaurants and years of preparing food from a simple need to create, she decided to combine exquisite food, breathtaking views and a unique atmosphere in her beautiful home in Ein Kerem, opposite the Judean hills. Today she hosts tourist and Israelis for ellite meals, cooking and baking workshops and culinary tours. Must book in advance.

data.name: Singer Cafe
data.ranking: #1 of 18 Coffee & Tea in Palestinian Territories
data.description: Just a short walk from Bethlehem you find the best coffee in Singer Cafe! We are in the process of moving to a new location and have temporarily moved our Cafe to our Al Jisser bar. The location is close to Suq al Shab and Edward Said Conservatory. You can find it on Google maps as Al Jisser. We serve great coffee, drinks and breakfast, lunch and simple dinner. Our Cafe / bar is owned by a Palestinian- Dutch couple. Kristel is also a tour guide and organizes excursions on demand for a reasonable price. Contact us for details.
data.address: Old City Street, Beit Sahour Palestinian Territories

data.name: Blue Hall Music
data.description: Beyond the stone walls of the Old City a shining pearl awaits in the charming alleyways of downtown Jerusalem, one which fuses past and future into one extraordinary experience. The Blue Hall Music is Jerusalem's newest restaurant and its oldest bar, offering premium quality experience in a warm and authentic atmosphere in the heart of downtown Jerusalem. The Blue Hall Music was built from music. We are the only place in Jerusalem hosts live music each night from 10pm with great artists in a variety of musical styles.
data.address: Nahalat Shivaa 12 16 2, Yo'el Moshe Salomon, Jerusalem 9463312 Israel

data.name: Andalucia
data.description: Andalucia is no longer a cocktail bar, but a kosher tapas restaurant, offering a variety of Spanish-inspired chef dishes. Here you can fall in love with the Spanish cuisine that was adapted to the Israeli audience, and enjoy Peruvian savory soups, mini burgers from entrecote meat with a special seasoning, empanadas filled with meat and raisins with sassy salsa next to it, original salads and more

Good music in the background and an addictive Jerusalemite vibes, guarantee you an exciting experience.

data.name: Happy Fish Restaurant
data.description: HAPPY FISH is a Mediterranean inspired fish restaurant located in the heart of Mamilla Avenue. The stairs nestled within the shops leads to a beautiful terrace overlooking the magnificent Jerusalem landscape and the Mamilla Avenue. The restaurant provides a dining experience with authentic and local atmosphere, cheerful service and good music. The meal begins with a selection of small homemade meze and house bread. It continues with a selection of fresh fish dishes prepared according to the guests desire. Authentic desserts and a rich bar menu that includes wine, alcohol and soft drink is available. The restaurant offers an excellent combination of central location, fresh Mediterranean cuisine and fair prices.
data.address: 11 King Solomon St. Mamilla Hotel, Jerusalem 94182 Israel

data.name: BeerBazaar Jerusalem
data.description: BeerBazaar, based in the heart of the Jerusalem Market, features over 100 local Israeli craft beers and delicious food prepared with fresh, local market ingredients. Our shelves are filled with Israeli beers from all over the country, from the Golan Heights down to the Negev desert. We have 10 specialty draft beers on tap, including seven of our house brews (Fat Cat, Doda, Bhindi, BlackJack, Wheatney, Gallagher and Esser). We offer free beer tastings and our menu contains various meat and vegetarian options. We're a unique place with an authentic atmosphere and an awesome staff. While the sun is out, we're a cozy, intimate beer garden, but at night we spread out into the market with tables and chairs.
data.address: Rehov Ets Khayim 3 Mahane Yehuda Covered Market, Jerusalem 9430001 Israel

data.name: Modern Restaurant
data.description: one of the best chef Restaurant in Israel. Contemporary, creative and personal culinary statement. The design of the restaurant, the exciting location in the Israel Museum, the View of the Valley of the Cross and views of the Knesset create a unique Jerusalem atmosphere. Modern dishes based on the old Jerusalem cuisine that developed outside the walls. Warm flavors of longing for distant lands. Park a chef and reassemble the recipes and create a modern cuisine with local flavors. Great ingredients, according to the season. MODERN offers business meals on Sundays-Thursdays at noon, a wide variety of wine, a collection of Israeli wines and wineries, depending on the preference of the audience and prices vary. Beer, champagne and alcohol. Menus vary, renew and refresh frequently depending on the season and availability in the markets. Modern team produces the spectacular museum grounds and on three levels, private and business events from 50 to 2000 people.
data.address: Israel Museum Jerusalem 11, Derekh Ruppin The Israel Museum, Jerusalem 9543500 Israel
